<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-653-782  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 653 782.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  July 1990 v7 n8 p55(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Defining the OSI model.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Spencer, Lloyd T.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Open Systems Interconnection model divides networkcommunications into seven layers corresponding to a set ofservices and protocols with rules for exchanging informationbetween computers and computer-based equipment.andP;  Networkperipherals that support the same set of protocol layers canintercommunicate providing each layer transfers data that conformsto the rules of its own protocol definition and providescommunications services to the next higher layer.andP;  The solephysical link is the network cable accessed through Layer 1.andP;  Thelayers are physical; data link; network; transport; session;presentation; and application.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     OSI StandardNetworksCommunications ModesProtocol.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   The OSI architecture. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>